<headline>Winter Weather Advisory issued April 18 at 3:37PM EDT until April 19 at 4:00AM EDT by NWS Detroit</headline>
<description>...WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 4 AM EDT
TUESDAY...
* WHAT...Snow expected. Total snow accumulations of 3 to 5
inches.
* WHERE...Huron, Sanilac, Tuscola, Lapeer and St. Clair Counties.
* WHEN...From noon today to 4 AM EDT Tuesday.
* IMPACTS...Plan on slippery road conditions. The hazardous
conditions could impact the evening commute.
* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...A period of wet heavy snow is expected late
this afternoon and evening primarily through 9 pm. Additional
light snowfall is then expected to persist into tonight,
particularly in the northern areas of the Thumb. The snowfall
rates are expected to be high enough to overcome mid April
daytime heating and allow for quick wet snow accumulations on
area roadways.</description>
<instruction>Slow down and use caution while traveling.</instruction>
